	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well I have read about a bard that shoud not sing ¿?¿? Its like a warrior that shoud not use the 2H weapons.<br><br>1. Choose the apropiate songs for every situation. Check the agrofactor for each of them.<br><br>2. Practice in SMALL groups against few mobs (1 or 2) so you can discern what happens when.<br><br>3. EVER tell or advice the healers (clerics or paladins...) of your vulnerability and agro issues. Remember that they tell YOU when they are running out of mana so you can change your strategie.<br><br>4. Do the same with the tanks so they TAUNT the monsters away from you. <br><br>5. On no-dungeon areas dont be afraid to run away using Selo and taking with you the train. Your group will finish them of one by one while you are running. Dont forget to use Jaxans to restore stammina. This kitting games can be very long...<br><br>6. Learn to make crowd control.<br><br>7. Combine songs with hand weapons.<br><br>8. Make sure you get the best buffs available and that you are in effect buffed.<br><br>9. Nobody said that beeing a bard was easy.<br><br><br><br>Pastrin, a happy 21 songs bard at Solusek Ro<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
