<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=969423157478></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f969423157478><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=969423157478>RE: HTH or 1H Slashing?</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=1315><span id= >Ayre</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>5 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 20th 12:12 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Depends on the situation.<br><br>Basically when you can first play string instruments (lvl 8) is when an instrument only attack with HTH becomes feasable (twist chords and hymn).  I used a chords, hymn, and bellow combination to kill wisps from lvl 11 (also at lvl 10 without the bellow).  I still used weapons predominantly at this time however.<br><br>At level 18-19? an instrument only attack definitely puts out more damage than weapons (my weapons being a thulian claw and Dragoon dirk) as you get Denons discord to add to the twist with a horn.<br><br>However weapons so far (lvl 27) still have their place.  In a group, I'm always with weapons in hand except during downtime.  Most of our group songs at my level only use the singing skill after all.  AE is also not appreciated in most situations.<br><br>Solo, chain/fear tactics still leave me when weapons in hand.  I generally use this with opponents that bash a lot.  I also play all instrument attack pretty often.  However the h2h skill is not a big part of your damage output in this situation.  I really see no reason to train h2h until your songs necessitate it.  :)  God I take a long to to say a simple sentence....<br><br>Ayre<br>The wee surfer bard.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
