<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9694231499996></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9694231499996><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=9694231499996>RE: HTH or 1H Slashing?</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 20th 12:12 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would suggest you train in as many weapon skills as possible. Your skill raises fast until lvl 45+ and its a pain to pick up a skill later in the game, when you by chance find a nice weapon, but you skill is lacking. <br><br>1hd slash - there are a lot of weapons out there that use this skill, so its a must have.<br><br>piercing - many bardic weapons use this skill, also a must. (e.g. you can dual wield a 1hd slash and a piercing weapon after lvl 17 and its easy to keep both skills maxed)<br><br>1hd blunt - less weapons for bards use this skill but a there are a few nice ones - so try to max this skill too.<br><br>hand to hand - aye, when you fight with your music instruments you use this skill. But from my experience, its more difficult to raise this skill (don't know why) and at later lvls you literally deal no damage with your punches. I punch for about 11 points max but usually for less (and one hit from a dual wielding / double attacking warrior does more damage then I do in a couple of attack sequences)<br> <br>When I use my music instruments in battle I prefer to stand aside and watch the battle, and e.g. target the messed mob, that in case mezz brakes and the chanter can not stun/remezz it in time, I can do a quick mezz or charm to safe his life - without having to target the mob first and therefore loosing precious time.<br><br>So train HTH but don't expect to much outcome in later lvls and make sure you train the other skills.<br><br>Hope this helps<br><br>Sgrobi Lutebasher<br>Bard 50 Strings, E'ci <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
