<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97346266428119></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97346266428119><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=97346266428119>RE: PvP as Bard</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Nov 5th 5:17 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As the previous poster mentioned, fighting a tank toe to toe, is not only stupid, but demonstrates how little you understand a Bard.  I agree with the fight him/her till half health and run to heal method.<br><br>For casters I usually fight with a whip-type weapon.  I have a Gnoll Hide Lariat and it works wonders on casters.  It interrupts their casting 85% of the time.  I also wouldn't rely too much on Bellows, it tends to not interrupt as expected.  If fighting a pet class, try to inflict as much damage as possible, while they cast their spells on you.  This should take about a minute.  Then kite the pet as far away from it's master as possible.  You see, the caster at this point is almost, if not completely out of mana.  Run back while twisting Selo's and Hymn of Restoration.  By the time you reach the caster, who at this point is sitting down medding and healing, thinking that his/her pet is chasing you out of the zone, smack them as hard as you can.  Use the same method of a low delay weapon to prevent them from getting away.  At this point the pet might have returned.  Ignore the pet and concentrate on killing the caster ASAP.  The pet will not inflict enough damage in time before you kill his master.  You will be standing there with the corpse of the caster and you will still be no less than 1/4 health.  I have used this technique numerous times.  Every once in a while you will run into a caster that really knows how to play his/her character and chances are that you will not be able to kill him/her, but they will not be able to kill you either.  Luckily this type of player is seldom found.  I also recommend starting caster characters to familiarize yourself with the class's weaknesses and strenghts.  The only reason I can beat Enchanters and Wizards with my Bard is because I play as an Enchanter and a Wizard too.  <br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
