<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96931438523429></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96931438523429><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=96931438523429>RE: PvP as Bard</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=834><span id=Sage>Ceredin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>15 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 18th 5:59 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>For fighting a tank you can use one of two methods, the honorable method, or the weasel method.<br><br>Honorable method: die like a fool<br><br>Weasel method: fight him until you're at about half health, try to get behind him as much as possible (he will be trying to do the exact same thing to you if he's any good). When you're at about half health, turn on Selo's and run like a coward. Don't zone, just go to where it'll take him a while to find you. Heal up with Hymn of Restoration using your lute. The tank will have only recovered a little bit of health, and you'll be at full health. This tactic is much less effective against paladins and rangers, but it still works.<br><br>For fighting casters, a completely different approach is required.<br><br>Use two weapons and at least one haste song. Leave the third song open so when you see him casting, you can bellow. This works well for interrupting spells. It is a great idea to use selo's if you're fighting someone who can root you, but you have to have it on before you get rooted. If you have selo's on, you can't be rooted (it used to be that selo's broke root, but not anymore). With any luck, the caster will begin to run, in which case you can easily kill him or her (gotta love selo's).<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
