<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9692784965540></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9692784965540><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=9692784965540>Qeynos, the best place for a starting bard</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=1597><span id= >Rezn</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>12 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 18th 8:01 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Qeynos, the perfect place for a starting bard.  There are many great quests and many other items to hunt within its grounds.  From level 1 to 2 (or level 1 to 3 if you prefer) you can do quests to level up.  Try the 'Watch Report' quest you can get from your own guild.  You'll make a little bit of silver and make nearly a full bubble of experience each time you complete it.  This is on your first level, of course.  You don't make as much during your second or third levels.  When you do this, just be sure to run the reports to Anehan and Behroe, on the docks.  This way, you won't have to zone.  You can do this until you get enough for your first (Or perhaps second) level song(s).  This is a great help to any starting bard.<br><br>The reason I love Qeynos so much is the amount of quests, and how you can level off them.  Above is just one of the minor examples.  If you want to do quests in order to make a bit of spare change (Nobody gives us tips for our singing, so we gotta do what we gotta do), try Behroe's quest.  You'll get a bit of faction, and a nice 'lil Veil which is decent armor for the starting bard.  Or, you could sell it for nearly a full gold piece, which isn't that bad compared to the copper pieces you get for whiskers and wings at the front gate.  Plus, the faction is priceless.  When I was through with Qeynos, everyone loved me.  The guards, my guild, the Knights of Freeport (Whom I've never come into contact with) were all warmly with me.  <br><br>There are plenty of other quests about that can help you make a bit 'o change.  Mail delivery from Surefall, Gnoll Teeth, Statue Delivery from Surefall, Tax Collecting, Crate 'o Arrows, and plenty of others are possible.  Try to make your own quest ring during your hunting periods.  It may make leveling much faster...<br><br>For instance, this was mine when I was a newbie bard in Qeynos.  He's now a level 48 bard in full plane armor...<br><br>1) Start out at the front gate in North Qeynos.<br>2) Go to the Cleric's guild of Rodcet Nife and get the Holy Water for Brother Ethel.<br>3) Head to the Qeynos Hills.  Kill any Rabid Wolves or Bears you see on your way for their pelts to give to the priestesses in Qeynos.<br>4) As you run by the West Karana zone, zone in and hand the Brother his water.  If you see the evil cleric up, kill him and hope for a rat ring to return.  Or at least his busted prayer beads.<br>5) Head back and go hunt in Blackburrow.  Collect as many gnoll teeth as possible.<br>6) When food or room is exhausted in your inventory, leave and head to Surefall Glade.<br>7) Sell, restock.<br>8) Get Bard Letter from the Bard in the Ranger Guild there.<br>9) Get the statue note from the druid in the druid's hut.<br>10) Head back to Blackburrow and continue to hunt, getting as many teeth as possible still.<br>11) When food/room is once again exhausted, head to Qeynos.<br>12) Deliver mail/statue letter/pelts/rat ring/prayer beads.  Re-start all of those quests.<br>13) Restock, repeat.<br><br>The only thing different about this quest ring now is that you have the Tunare statue to deliver to the druid back in his druid hut.  Re-do his quest when you stop there again.  You get a bit for returning the statue to him.<br><br>Using this ring, I leveled from 1 to 10 here in two days.<br><br>There are also plenty of other high level quests.  The broken lute quest takes you to south Karana and nets you two platinum and your level six song (A five platinum value!).  The Shining Star of Light quest is kind of fun as well, but you'll have to have higher faction with the priests of Rodcet Nife (Thus the delivering of the holy water, rat rings, and prayer beads).<br><br>All in all, this is a great place to begin.  The hunting is nice, the quests are plentiful, and the people are actually some of the best I've interacted with in any newbie area.  I often come back and do player run quests, since its quite a bit of fun to do, and it helps out the new players.<br><br>Oh, and for any other information regarding these quests, check AllaKhazam's quest section.  It explains just about everything needed.<br>&nbsp;<br>Ensis Arament</td></tr>
