<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96813124217087></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96813124217087><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=96813124217087>20-24 lake of Ill omen</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=206><span id=Scholar>Kasparytus</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>34 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 5th 1:20 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Another nice place to solo lvl your bard is along the beach in the lake of Ill omen. The location that I speak of is along the beach near the sarnek fortress (staring around the front enterance) and you can follow that all the to the area before the zone to Firona if you like..though I perfer to turn around before that Again this is a kiting duty and relativly boring work..but since your dropping reds and not sharing the exp its well worth it. It requires one to arrange the overhead camara so that you can have anice few of you running up and down the beach with your prey in tow without many changes in camera angle or zoom which the game with do for you if your angle is off. <br><br>Its a pretty simple hunt really...make sure to have Selos, hymn, bellow, and the jig song memed and hotkeyed then find a red critter to kite...there are 4 main types about...goblin warlords, charrbone skeles, Sarnek recruits, and sabrecats. Dont go after the sabrekats cuase they run faster than your normal gate and you will have to keep switching between selos and bellow..which is less effecient. I perfer to kite the gobs because they will run around 25% health. Sarneks also run but dont make any sound when hit which is annoying if you use the "hiss" of the creatures to reset your bellow. The skeles are tough, hit hard and never flee but do make a cradcking sound when hit. Once you select your prey run up and down beach bellowing ..jump once or twice when if the critter gets too close..you shouldnt need to use selos unless you stop, want to turn around, or run out of stamina from jumping. if you have your lute quipt throw in a hymn and jig when you decide to turn around. its really easy..slighty boring and I rarly even lose a bubble of health. <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
